<p>I am trying to create a subdomain but it just won't work the subdomain admin.dev-talk.eu is just getting redirected to dev-talk.eu. This are my 2 files in /etc/httpd/sites-avaible (im using centos 7)</p>  <p>dev-talk.eu:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;      ServerAdmin ****@live.nl     ServerName dev-talk.eu     ServerAlias www.dev-talk.eu     DocumentRoot /var/www/dev-talk.eu/public_html     &lt;Directory /&gt;             Options FollowSymLinks             AllowOverride None     &lt;/Directory&gt;     &lt;Directory /var/www/dev-talk.eu/public_html&gt;             Options FollowSymLinks MultiViews             AllowOverride All             Order allow,deny             allow from all     &lt;/Directory&gt;  &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And this is for admin.dev-talk.eu:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;     ServerAdmin ***@live.nl     ServerName admin.dev-talk.eu     DocumentRoot /var/www/dev-talk.eu/public_html/admin      &lt;Directory /var/www/dev-talk.eu/public_html/admin&gt;             Options FollowSymLinks MultiViews             AllowOverride All             Order allow,deny             allow from all     &lt;/Directory&gt; &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; </code></pre>  <p>DNS: <a href="http://puu.sh/kwPHn/9dd36461e3.PNG" rel="nofollow">http://puu.sh/kwPHn/9dd36461e3.PNG</a></p>